          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Forty Hours is Full Time Act of 201</strong><b>7</b></p> <p> This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code, with respect to the employer mandate to provide health care coverage, to: (1) modify the formula for calculating the number of full-time employees employed by an applicable large employer subject to the mandate; and (2) define a &quot;full-time employee&quot; as an employee who is employed on average at least 40 hours per week (currently, 30 hours).</p>]]></text>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
